|Cl_G(g)=|G|/|C_G(g)|
|S_n|=n!
|Cl_G(g)|=\frac{n!}{\Pi r^{n_r}*n_r!}
r
n_r
g=(1,..,n)
n
|Cl_G(g)|=\frac{n!}{n}=(n-1)!
|C_G(g)|=\frac{|G|}{|Cl_G(g)|}=\frac{n!}{(n-1)!}=n
\sigma(12\cdots n)\sigma^{-1}=(\sigma(1)\sigma(2)\cdots\sigma(n))=(12\cdots n)
